✅ MongoDB JSON Querying Practical (Ubuntu – Mongo Shell)

Create JSON → Import JSON → Display Electronics → Count > 10,000

✅ 1. Create JSON File (products.json)
Run:

gedit products.json


Paste:

[
  {"name": "Laptop", "category": "Electronics", "price": 55000},
  {"name": "Phone", "category": "Electronics", "price": 12000},
  {"name": "Shirt", "category": "Clothing", "price": 1500},
  {"name": "TV", "category": "Electronics", "price": 30000},
  {"name": "Watch", "category": "Accessories", "price": 9000}
]


Save → Close.

✅ 2. Import JSON Into MongoDB
Run in terminal:

mongoimport --db product_db --collection products --file products.json --jsonArray

Expected:

5 document(s) imported successfully


✅ 3. Open Mongo Shell

mongosh

✅ 4. Switch to Database

use product_db

Output:

switched to db product_db


✅ 5. Display All Electronics Products

db.products.find({category: "Electronics"}).pretty()

✅ 6. Count Products Priced Above ₹10,000

db.products.countDocuments({price: {$gt: 10000}})

Expected:

3


✅ 7. Exit Mongo Shell

exit